   Ranunculus japonicus with flap-like nectary scales to Halerpestes
   ruthenica and Batrachium bungei with cup-like and ring-like nectary
   scales. Visitation rate, visit duration and pollinator efficiency of
   each group were compared to distinguish true pollinators from visitors.
   Regression analysis was also used to identify potential correlation
   between different petal nectary scale shapes and morphological traits of
